Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fneed-based-financial-aid%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneed-based%20and%20merit-based%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Sounds%20simple%2C%20right%3F%20It's%20not.%20While%20both%20types%20come%20from%20the%20college%20after%20a%20student%20applies%2C%20they're%20awarded%20for%20different%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeed-based%20scholarships%20are%20determined%20by%20the%20student's%20(or%2C%20more%20accurately%2C%20their%20parents')%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-stocks-recover-after-bank-earnings-inflation-data-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20situation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20merit%20scholarships%20reward%20students%20for%20their%20accomplishments%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20that's%20grades%2C%20leadership%2C%20or%20athletic%20abilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%20confused%3F%20Don't%20worry%2C%20you're%20not%20alone.%20For%20now%2C%20let's%20stick%20to%20merit%20scholarships%20since%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteenagers-travel-with-mom-family-vacations-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteenage%20twins%3C%2Fa%3E%20didn't%20qualify%20for%20need-based%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22756c7b02-3eba-4b8c-945f-04d4bfae84ec%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20you%20qualify%20for%20merit%20scholarships%20from%20the%20college%20you%20apply%20to%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20question%20often%20comes%20up%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffree-our-feeds-takes-on-billionaire-controlled-social-media-platforms-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20groups%2C%20and%20honestly%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20anyone%20knows%20the%20definitive%20answer.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20speculation%2C%20but%20unless%20someone%20from%20the%20college%20admissions%20office%20directly%20explains%20why%20your%20kid%20received%20a%20merit%20scholarship%2C%20it's%20really%20just%20guessing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20what%20I%20understand%2C%20merit%20scholarships%20are%20based%20on%20how%20much%20a%20college%20wants%20your%20child%20to%20attend.%20If%20your%20child%20has%20qualities%20that%20the%20college%20values%2C%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20offer%20a%20scholarship%20to%20encourage%20attendance.%20Some%20parents%20compare%20merit%20scholarships%20to%20Kohl's%20Cash%20or%20coupons%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%2C%20incentives%20to%20choose%20that%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224309ad3f-5293-4ae8-9dba-bc06760aa0c3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESomehow%2C%20they%20received%20different%20merit%20scholarships%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20boy%2Fgirl%20twins%20seemed%20to%20have%20qualities%20colleges%20were%20seeking.%20Both%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaughter-overwhelmed-work-on-college-applications-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bhigh-achieving%20students%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20they%20took%20advanced%20placement%20(AP)%20and%20honors%20classes.%20They%20were%20in%20the%20National%20Honors%20Society%2C%20with%20high%20GPAs%20that%20differed%20by%20only%200.20%20points.%20They%20were%20also%20leaders%3B%20both%20were%20club%20presidents%20and%20captains%20of%20their%20respective%20tennis%20teams%20(boys'%20and%20girls'%20teams%20were%20separate).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20sharing%20this%20to%20brag%20(though%20I'm%20incredibly%20proud!)%20but%20to%20give%20you%20an%20idea%20of%20the%20kinds%20of%20achievements%20that%20colleges%20might%20look%20for%20when%20awarding%20merit%20scholarships.%20Many%20colleges%20also%20like%20high%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdartmouth-brings-back-sat-act-standardized-test-requirement-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESAT%20or%20ACT%20scores%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20neither%20of%20them%20submitted%20scores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20twins%20applied%20to%20seven%20of%20the%20same%20colleges%2C%20and%20each%20offered%20them%20different%20amounts%20of%20merit%20scholarships.%20Naturally%2C%20you'd%20think%20the%20twin%20with%20the%200.20%20higher%20GPA%20would%20receive%20more%20scholarship%20money%2C%20right%3F%20That%20would%20make%20sense%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20what%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20shared%20this%20observation%20with%20a%20friend%2C%20they%20suggested%20that%20the%20school%20might%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20increase%20enrollment%20for%20a%20specific%20gender%20since%20my%20twins%20are%20of%20different%20genders.%20It%20also%20could%20have%20been%20influenced%20by%20the%20majors%20they%20were%20interested%20in%20or%20the%20clubs%20they%20belonged%20to.%20Who%20knows%3F%20Not%20me!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22330cdbd2-e86f-4bdc-b1ab-eb5a81fcd255%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETheir%20merit%20scholarships%20were%20very%20different%20at%20some%20schools%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20schools%2C%20the%20difference%20was%20between%20%241%2C000%20and%20%242%2C000%2C%20which%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20but%20not%20when%20you%20consider%20that%20some%20private%20college%20tuitions%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-cost-of-college-room-and-board-is-rising-faster-than-tuition-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroom%20and%20board%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20over%20%2490%2C000%20per%20year.%20Suddenly%2C%20%241%2C000%20seems%20like%20a%20small%20dent%20or%20pennies%20in%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20discrepancy%20in%20merit%20scholarships%20they%20received%20was%20at%20a%20small%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-kings-college-financial-troubles-small-christian-college-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliberal%20arts%20college%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20twin%20was%20awarded%20%2413%2C000%20a%20year%20more%20than%20the%20other%2C%20which%20is%20%2452%2C000%20over%20four%20years%20of%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E