5-01%2Fv118ruv8_karun-nair-x_625x300_12_January_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Ficc-champions-trophy-2025%2Fsomeone-averages-700-on-karun-nairs-champions-trophy-snub-bccis-blunt-verdict-7502773%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20amassing%20more%20than%20700%20runs%20in%20the%20Vijay%20Hazare%20Trophy%2C%20Vidarbha%20captain%20Karun%20Nair%20did%20not%20find%20a%20place%20in%20the%20team.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Ficc-champions-trophy-2025%2Fsomeone-averages-700-on-karun-nairs-champions-trophy-snub-bccis-blunt-verdict-7502773%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20US%20exit%20from%20NATO%20under%20Trump%20would%20likely%20trigger%20a%20legal%20showdown%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trump%2C%20NATO%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6424099eed593e00183f0682%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20criticized%20NATO%20allies%20and%20warned%20he%20could%20try%20to%20withdraw%20the%20US%20from%20the%20alliance.%3Cp%3ENICHOLAS%20KAMM%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPresident-elect%20Trump%20has%20warned%20he%20may%20try%20to%20withdraw%20the%20US%20from%20NATO.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAny%20attempt%20would%20counter%20Congress%20and%20venture%20into%20uncharted%20legal%20waters.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20legislative%20expert%20saw%20signs%20that%20could%20favor%20Congress%20in%20this%20largely%20untested%20area.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20privately%20warned%20that%20he%20might%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaw-to-keep-trump-from-leaving-nato-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithdraw%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20US%20from%20NATO.%20He%20complained%20that%20other%20alliance%20members%20weren't%20contributing%20their%20fair%20share%20of%20defense%20spending%2C%20which%20left%20American%20taxpayers%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nato-budget-is-funded-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epick%20up%20the%20tab%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECongress%20thought%20otherwise.%20It%20added%20a%20special%20provision%20in%20the%202020%20National%20Defense%20Authorization%20Act%2C%20which%20sets%20funding%20for%20the%20US%20military.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fuscode.house.gov%2Fview.xhtml%3Freq%3D(title%3A22%2520section%3A1928f%2520edition%3Aprelim)%2520OR%2520(granuleid%3AUSC-prelim-title22-section1928f)%26f%3Dtreesort%26edition%3Dprelim%26num%3D0%26jumpTo%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESection%201250A%3C%2Fa%3E%20specifies%20that%20the%20president%20cannot%20unilaterally%20withdraw%20America%20from%20NATO%20without%20an%20act%20of%20Congress%2C%20or%20unless%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20Senate%20concur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShould%20Trump%20follow%20through%20during%20his%20second%20term%2C%20which%20starts%20Monday%2C%20the%20withdrawal%20would%20fall%20into%20a%20legal%20gray%20area%20likely%20to%20be%20settled%20in%20court%20and%20that%20may%20favor%20Congress.%20The%20problem%20is%20that%20while%20the%20Constitution%20specifies%20that%20the%20president%20has%20the%20power%20to%20negotiate%20treaties%2C%20it%20doesn't%20say%20whether%20he%20has%20the%20power%20to%20break%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20Congress%20has%20to%20some%20extent%20regulated%20the%20President's%20withdrawal%20from%20a%20treaty%20in%20the%20past%2C%20Section%201250A%20is%20the%20first%20statute%20in%20which%20Congress%20has%20prohibited%20unilateral%20presidential%20withdrawal%20from%20a%20treaty%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FLSB%2FLSB11256%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Karen%20Sokol%2C%20a%20legislative%20attorney%20for%20the%20Congressional%20Research%20Service%2C%20which%20analyzes%20issues%20for%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Founding%20Fathers%20were%20rightly%20proud%20that%20they%20created%20a%20government%20of%20checks%20and%20balances%2C%20where%20neither%20the%20executive%2C%20legislative%20or%20judicial%20branches%20could%20monopolize%20power.%20But%20they%20probably%20would%20be%20less%20than%20thrilled%20with%20the%20dispute%20over%20NATO%2C%20which%20America%20was%20instrumental%20in%20forming%2075%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20a%20devastated%20Europe%20appeared%20easy%20prey%20for%20Soviet%20conquest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENormally%2C%20the%20executive%20branch%20handles%20most%20foreign%20policy%20and%20national%20security%20matters%20such%20as%20negotiating%20treaties%2C%20though%20Congress%20exercises%20considerable%20clout%20through%20defense%20budgets%2C%20ratifying%20treaties%2C%20and%20approving%20arms%20sales.%20Powers%20between%20the%20executive%20and%20legislative%20branches%20are%20delineated%20clearly%20enough%20that%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20the%20system%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20executive%20and%20legislature%20can't%20agree%2C%20the%20courts%20are%20supposed%20to%20step%20in.%20Yet%20of%20all%20the%20myriad%20issues%20that%20end%20up%20in%20American%20courts%2C%20foreign%20policy%20is%20the%20area%20that%20judges%20are%20most%20reluctant%20to%20touch.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20withdrawing%20from%20NATO%2C%20the%20courts%20will%20search%20for%20legal%20precedents%20in%20an%20area%20that%20lacks%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20has%20long%20maintained%20that%20it%20can%20withdraw%20from%20treaties%20absent%20Congressional%20opposition%2C%20such%20as%20when%20the%20Carter%20Administration%20withdrew%20from%20a%20mutual%20defense%20treaty%20with%20Taiwan%2C%20which%20Senator%20Barry%20Goldwater%20and%20other%20members%20of%20Congress%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupreme.justia.com%2Fcases%2Ffederal%2Fus%2F444%2F996%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappealed%20to%20the%20courts%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20declined%20to%20weigh%20in%20on%20the%20dispute%2C%26quot%3B%20Sokol%20noted.%20%26quot%3BWith%20a%20plurality%20of%20the%20Justices%20concurring%20in%20the%20judgment%20to%20dismiss%20the%20complaint%2C%20concluding%20that%20the%20case%20presented%20a%20political%20question%20that%20was%20properly%20addressed%20by%20the%20political%20branches%20rather%20than%20the%20judiciary%20%E2%80%94%20a%20determination%20that%20is%20not%20uncommon%20in%20cases%20involving%20separation-%20of-powers%20disputes%20in%20areas%20of%20foreign%20policy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20special%20operators%20skydive%20from%20an%20MC-130J%20Commando%20II%20aircraft%20during%20a%20December%20exercise%20with%20a%20NATO%20ally.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67892fa050dfd88e193ebd22%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20special%20operators%20skydive%20from%20an%20MC-130J%20Commando%20II%20aircraft%20during%20a%20December%20exercise%20with%20a%20NATO%20ally.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20Trump's%20first%20term%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20published%20an%20opinion%20that%20asserted%20treaty%20withdrawal%20is%20an%20exclusive%20presidential%20power%20that%20Congress%20cannot%20restrict.%20And%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20ruled%20that%20the%20executive%20branch%20has%20the%20authority%20to%20recognize%20foreign%20governments%2C%20even%20though%20that%20power%20is%20not%20specified%20in%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20past%20cases%20suggest%20that%20the%20courts%20may%20reject%20this%20argument.%20Sokol%20points%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconstitutioncenter.org%2Fthe-constitution%2Fsupreme-court-case-library%2Fyoungstown-sheet-tube-co-v-sawyer-steel-seizure-case%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1952%20Youngstown%20Steel%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20against%20President%20Harry%20S.%20Truman's%20attempt%20to%20seize%20steel%20mills%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-invasion-at-incheon-helped-turn-tide-during-korean-war-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKorean%20War%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20this%20violated%20the%20intent%20of%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnder%20the%20Youngstown%20framework%2C%20courts%20assess%20presidential%20claims%20of%20authority%20based%20on%20what%20Congress%20has%E2%80%94or%20has%20not%E2%80%94said%20about%20the%20matter%2C%26quot%3B%20Sokol%20wrote.%20By%20that%20standard%2C%20Congress%20has%20expressed%20its%20intent%20that%20the%20US%20remain%20in%20NATO%20by%20passing%20Section%201250A.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESokol%20also%20believes%20that%20the%20courts%20may%20reject%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20assertion%20that%20the%20executive%20branch%20alone%20can%20decide%20to%20withdraw%20from%20treaties.%20%26quot%3BA%20court%20may%20find%20a%20President's%20claim%20of%20exclusive%20constitutional%20power%20to%20withdraw%20from%20a%20treaty%20to%20be%20unpersuasive%20given%20that%20the%20Constitution%20is%20silent%20about%20treaty%20withdrawal%20powers%20and%20that%20Article%20II%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconstitution.congress.gov%2Fconstitution%2Farticle-2%2F%2523article-2-section-2%3A~%3Atext%3DHe%2520shall%2520have%2520Power%252C%2520by%2520and%2520with%2520the%2520Advice%2520and%2520Consent%2520of%2520the%2520Senate%252C%2520to%2520make%2520Treaties%252C%2520provided%2520two%2520thirds%2520of%2520the%2520Senators%2520present%2520concur%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20makes%3C%2Fa%3E%20treaty%20entry%20a%20power%20shared%20between%20the%20President%20and%2