2C%20surrounded%20by%20Stanford%20University%20and%20the%20headquarters%20of%20a%20slew%20of%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20in%20the%20world%2C%20the%20home%20is%20likely%20worth%20close%20to%20%244%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20home%20is%20large%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0in%20the%20mid-1980s%20the%20couple%20added%20a%20second%20story%20to%20the%20house%20to%20accommodate%20four%20additional%20bedrooms%20and%20two%20bathrooms%20as%20their%20family%20grew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20they%20rebuilt%20the%20single-story%20cottage%20in%20their%20backyard%20%E2%80%94%20also%20known%20as%20an%20accessory%20dwelling%20unit%20%E2%80%94%20to%20include%20a%20bedroom%2C%20kitchen%2C%20and%20bathroom.%20They've%20rented%20out%20the%20cottage%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Allens%20have%20no%20plans%20to%20sell%20their%20home%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20larger%20than%20what%20they%20need.%20That's%20because%20they%20plan%20to%20eventually%20downsize%20to%20their%20backyard%20cottage%20and%20rent%20out%20the%20main%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Allens%20aren't%20alone%20in%20relying%20on%20an%20ADU%20for%20housing%20in%20their%20older%20age.%20Backyard%20tiny%20homes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0or%20other%20accessory%20units%20in%20basements%20or%20attics%20%E2%80%94%20are%20an%20increasingly%20common%20way%20for%20homeowners%20to%20add%20living%20space%2C%20boost%20the%20value%20of%20their%20property%20and%20earn%20extra%20income%20through%20rent%2C%20and%20even%20create%20a%20place%20to%20age%20in.%20California%20is%20one%20of%2014%20states%20that%20have%20broadly%20legalized%20ADUs%20and%20more%20than%2060%2C000%20have%20been%20permitted%20in%20the%20state%20since%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2204ef842d-cd35-4ad3-a2e8-aac149bbdbfd%5C%22%3EWhen%20selling%20will%20cost%20you%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20having%20a%20backyard%20home%20to%20downsize%20to%2C%20it%20doesn't%20make%20much%20financial%20sense%20for%20the%20Allens%20to%20sell%20their%20property%20and%20buy%20a%20smaller%20home%20to%20age%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20sold%20the%20property%2C%20they'd%20be%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-homeowners-capital-gains-tax-home-sales-retirement-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehefty%20capital%20gains%20taxes%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20apply%20to%20couples%20who%20make%20more%20than%20%24500%2C000%20in%20profit%20and%20individuals%20who%20make%20more%20than%20%24250%2C000.%20They'd%20also%20likely%20have%20to%20pay%20significantly%20higher%20property%20taxes%20if%20they%20purchased%20a%20new%20home%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20a%20relatively%20high%20interest%20rate%20on%20any%20new%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20California%20homeowners%20who%20purchased%20their%20properties%20decades%20ago%2C%20the%20Allens%20benefit%20from%20exceedingly%20low%20property%20taxes%20as%20a%20result%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.boe.ca.gov%2Fproptaxes%2Fpdf%2Fpub29.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProposition%2013%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20mandates%20that%20property%20taxes%20are%20just%20one%20percent%20of%20the%20home's%20purchase%20price%20and%20can't%20rise%20by%20more%20than%20two%20percent%20each%20year%20until%20the%20next%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20California%20law%20has%20contributed%20to%20the%20so-called%20homeownership%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fdigest%2Fapr05%2Flock-effect-californias-proposition-13%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elock-in%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20intensifies%20over%20time%20as%20home%20values%20rise%20and%20the%20property%20taxes%20someone%20would%20have%20to%20pay%20on%20a%20newly%20purchased%20home%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20living%20in%20this%20%244%20million%20house%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20downsize%20because%20it's%20kind%20of%20not%20worth%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Allen%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe'd%20have%20to%20pay%20so%20much%20in%20taxes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllen's%20story%20reflects%20a%20broader%20trend%20of%20boomer%20homeowners%20who've%20grown%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fresearch%2Fpdf%2F2024-Baby-Boomer-Consumer-Research.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esignificant%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20their%20home%20equity.%20And%20she's%20quick%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20she's%20both%20benefited%20from%20and%20perpetuated%20%26quot%3Bgenerational%20wealth%26quot%3B%20through%20homeownership.%20She%20could%20afford%20her%20own%20%2412%2C500%20downpayment%20only%20with%20help%20from%20her%20mother.%20In%20turn%2C%20she's%20helped%20her%20five%20adult%20children%20with%20their%20down%20payments.%20But%20the%20Allens'%20kids%20have%20all%20left%20California%20to%20live%20in%20other%20states%20%E2%80%94%20Texas%2C%20Idaho%2C%20Utah%2C%20and%20Nevada%20%E2%80%94%20where%20housing%20is%20more%20affordable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZillow%20estimates%20the%20Allens'%20property%20is%20worth%20about%20%243.1%20million%2C%20while%20Redfin%20puts%20it%20at%20nearly%20%243.5%20million.%20Allen%20thinks%20it%20could%20be%20sold%20for%20closer%20to%20%244%20million%2C%20based%20on%20what%20similar%20homes%20in%20her%20neighborhood%20have%20fetched%20in%20recent%20months.%20A%20much%20smaller%20home%20down%20the%20street%20from%20the%20Allens'%20house%20sold%20for%20%243.6%20million%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20spend%20three%20to%20%244%20million%20for%20a%20house%2C%20knock%20it%20flat%2C%20and%20build%20a%20big%20new%20house%20on%20the%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllen%20still%20works%20part-time%20for%20the%20East%20Palo%20Alto%20school%20district%20doing%20tech%20support%2C%20but%20her%20husband%2C%20a%20former%20patent%20attorney%2C%20is%20fully%20retired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Allen's%20husband%2C%20who%20has%20Parkinson's%20disease%2C%20develops%20dementia%20and%20she%20can%20no%20longer%