diet%20and%20weight.%20We%20know%20diet%20can%20influence%20colorectal%20cancer%20risk%2C%20and%20it's%20something%20people%20can%20fix%2C%20to%20a%20degree.%20Plus%2C%20our%20diets%20%3Cem%3Ehave%3C%2Fem%3E%20changed.%20These%20days%20we%20all%20consume%20more%20sugar%2C%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ultra-processed-foods-impact-your-body-calories-weight-gain-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultra-processed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20more%20oil%20and%20butter%2C%20while%20moving%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20doctors%20say%20the%20trend%20we're%20seeing%20now%20defies%20neat%20categories%20of%20genetics%20or%20lifestyle%2C%20and%20it's%20baffling.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOther%20factors%20are%20clearly%20messing%20with%20our%20digestive%20systems%2C%20but%20they're%20tough%20to%20pinpoint.%20Pollution%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastics-found-in-human-testicles-what-to-do-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicroplastics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20artificial%20light%20%E2%80%94%20all%20are%20pervasive%20in%20society%2C%20yet%20very%20tricky%20to%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20recent%20research%2C%20we%20are%20starting%20to%20get%20a%20better%20picture%20of%20why%20young%20colon%20cancer%20cases%20are%20rising%2C%20and%20we're%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20some%20pretty%20big%20results%20that%20may%20uncover%20better%20ways%20to%20prevent%20and%20treat%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224fd32dc3-f9e7-4df2-ad8b-752fd34ce093%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYoung%20colon%20cancer%20is%20getting%20deadlier%20and%20more%20common%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20shifted%20in%20the%201960s.%20Everyone%20born%20after%201960%20has%20a%20higher%20colon%20cancer%20risk%20than%20previous%20generations.%20This%20phenomenon%20is%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bbirth%20cohort%20effect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20rise%20that%20we're%20seeing%20cannot%20just%20be%20accounted%20for%20by%20inherited%20differences%2C%26quot%3B%20Dana%20Farber%20colon%20cancer%20researcher%20Dr.%20Marios%20Giannakis%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20young%20colon%20cancer%20rates%20have%20been%20rising%20about%203%25%20every%20year%20since%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20according%20to%20National%20Cancer%20Institute%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FS2Ic2%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Colon%20cancer%20rates%20are%20rising%20among%20young%20people%20around%20the%20world%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221363%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20think%20since%20genetics%20haven't%20changed%2C%20the%20cancers%20that%20are%20increasing%20are%20environmentally%20based%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20William%20Dahut%2C%20the%20chief%20science%20officer%20at%20the%20American%20Cancer%20Society%2C%20said%20during%20a%20recent%20briefing%20to%20reporters.%20%26quot%3BExactly%20what's%20doing%20it%20is%20really%20%E2%80%94%20more%20research%20is%20needed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20cancer%20centers%20in%20the%20US%20are%20opening%20units%20to%20investigate%20this%20trend.%20In%202018%2C%20Memorial%20Sloan%20Kettering%20in%20New%20York%20opened%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20center%20for%20%26quot%3Byoung-onset%26quot%3B%20colorectal%20cancer%20patients.%20Dana%20Farber%20in%20Boston%2C%20Mass%20General%2C%20MD%20Anderson%20Cancer%20Center%2C%20and%20Columbia%20University%20Irving%20Medical%20Center%20followed%20close%20behind%2C%20all%20opening%20special%20programs%20for%20young%20colon%20cancer%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20CDC%20took%20action%2C%20lowering%20the%20age%20of%20recommended%20colon%20cancer%20screening%20from%2050%20to%2045.%20It's%20an%20effort%20to%20catch%20more%20young%20colon%20cancer%20cases%20sooner%2C%20upping%20the%20odds%20of%20people%20surviving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20isn't%20a%20uniquely%20American%20issue.%20Wealthy%20countries%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20seeing%20similar%20spikes.%20New%20Zealand%2C%20Chile%2C%20Norway%2C%20and%20Turkey%20are%20among%2027%20countries%20recording%20record-high%20rates%20of%20young%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287228df1-0a6a-4d94-929b-7e35a013efe7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDiets%20matter%20%E2%80%94%20to%20an%20extent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22person%20holding%20shaft%20of%20wheat%2C%20farming%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678a96a32fcded5e9073b120%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Fedele%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20dismiss%20the%20role%20our%20changing%20food%20landscape%20has%20played.%20We%20are%20undoubtedly%20eating%20worse%20than%20our%20grandparents%20did%20100%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20fiber%2C%20for%20example.%20Found%20in%20abundance%20in%20whole%20plant%20foods%20like%20beans%2C%20it%20is%20a%20nutrient%20clearly%20associated%20with%20lower%20risk%20of%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20foods%20in%20US%20supermarkets%20%E2%80%94%20prepackaged%20for%20our%20convenience%20%E2%80%94%20tend%20to%20have%20fiber%20stripped%20out%20during%20processing%2C%20and%20extra%20salt%2C%20sugar%2C%20and%20oils%20added%20in%20to%20make%20them%20more%20palatable%20and%20shelf-stable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20started%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20World%20War%20II%2C%20when%20industrial%20processing%20and%20factory%20farming%20took%20hold%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEssentially%20we%20redeployed%20what%20had%20allowed%20the%20United%20States%20and%20allies%20to%20prevail%20in%20that%20war%20to%20non-military%20applications%2C%20and%20it%20completely%20transformed%20agriculture%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20David%20Katz%2C%20a%20leading%20expert%20in%20chronic%20disease%20prevention%20and%20nutrition%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20only%20have%20a%20certain%20total%20number%20of%20calories%20you%20can%20eat%20per%20day%2C%20and%20if%20a%20higher%20percentage%20of%20those%20is%20made%20up%20of%20hamburgers%20and%20Pop-Tarts%2C%20then%20a%20lower%20percentage%20ipso%20facto%20is%20made%20up%20of%20lentils%20and%20all%20the%20other%20good%20stuff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Why%20more%20young%20people%20are%20getting%20cancer%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FR8bxYzOK-puACk8ZV.html%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EUltra-processed%20foods%20now%20account%20for%20a%20significant%20proportion%20of%20what%20we%20eat.%20Excess%20sugar%2C%20salt%2C%20and%20chemicals%20lurk%20in%20pasta%20sauce%2C%20breakfast%20cereals%2C%20and%20salad%20dressing.%20Brown%20bread%20labeled%20%26quot%3Bheart%20healthy%26quot%3B%20can%20have%20a%20higher%20sugar%20content%20than%20white%20Wonderbread.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpsetting%20the%20balance%20of%20nutrients%20in%20our%20guts%20has%20consequences.%20Compounds%20that%20aren't%20necessarily%20harmful%20in%20moderation%2C%20like%20omega-6%20fatty%20acids%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fare-seed-oils-dangerous-for-your-health-inflammation-evidence-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseed%20oils%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20take%20up%20a%20disproportionate%20part%20of%20our%20diets.%20That%20can%20lead%20to%20inflammation%2C%20infection%2C%20and%20diseases%20like%20diabetes%2C%20heart%20disease%2C%20and%2C%20yes%2C%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20microbiome%20is%20not%20just%20about%20what%20you%20eat.%20It's%20influenced%20by%20myriad%20factors%2C%20from%20how%20you%20were%20born%20to%20your%20work%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d1fc0de9-cc98-4233-b2ff-d3ed77535cd9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20else%20is%20going%20on%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22bright%20night%20lights%20of%20the%20city%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678a9619ae09223df2ba775c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBim%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20and%20lab%20scientists%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%20for%20this%20story%20all%20said%20the%20rise%20in%20millennials%20getting%20colon%20cancer%20likely%20won't%20be%20attributed%20to%20one%20single%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShuji%20Ogino%2C%20an%20epidemiology%20professor%20at%20Harvard%20Medical%20School%2C%20has%20been%20studying%20young%20colon%20cancer%20cases%20across%20the%20world.%20He%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D1c20d71fa38daf2e24609e95c1071d0f131d7b348557c3c5cb4b32296ab0b1ab%26postID%3D67897b6a6f72cdb8614c4970%26postSlug%3Dcolon-cancer-environmental-causes-microplastics-antibiotics-sleep-2025-1%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41571-022-00672-8.epdf%253Fsharing_token%253D1umLnn8X8BYzX5QTMHyArtRgN0jAjWel9jnR3ZoTv0Mbf4RPi-ocNFWHJz8DUBZsAPhKJF2UqgYLHsA0Cpbtq9pHyF5VY4_JUzOCW23Ny67AuPivP2QGjseGKUadh2IPLERt0L07AH5dSEBqCheSrvp_NMPuByyxFdBZ3yftAdU%25253D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Nature%20that%20showed%20the%20early%20life%20%26quot%3Bexposome%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20diet%2C%20lifestyle%2C%20environment%2C%20exposures%20%E2%80%94%20has%20changed%20dramatically%2C%20becoming%20conducive%20to%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20introduced%20lots%20of%20new%20things%20to%20our%20environment%20without%20knowing%20the%20ramifications.%20Now%2C%20we're%20starting%20to%20see%20the%20long-term%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20as%20simple%20as%20artificial%20light%20could%20play%20a%20role.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20something%20no%20human%20being%20experienced%20200%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Ogino%20said.%20Lights%20allow%20us%20to%20work%20and%20socialize%20at%20all%20hours%2C%20impacting%20how%20our%20body%20clocks%20regulate%20hormones%20and%20metabolism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Heinz-Josef%20Lenz%2C%20co-lead%20of%20the%20gastrointestinal%20cancer%20program%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%20cancer%20center%2C%20is%20also%20studying%20how%20the%20environment%20may%20be%20damaging%20our%20DNA%20in%20ways%20we%20don't%20yet%20understand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20data%20so%20far%20suggests%20the%20trend%20of%20more%20younger%20folks%20developing%20colon%20cancer%20isn't%20genetic%2C%20but%20our%20genes%20may%20affect%20how%20we%20respond%20to%20our%20exposures%20%E2%80%94%20the%20processed%20food%20we%20eat%2C%20the%20antibiotics%20we%20take%2C%20and%20the%20polluted%20air%20we%20breathe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20are%2016%20years%20old%20or%2020%20years%20old%2C%20you%20cannot%20blame%20it%20on%20diet%20or%20exercise%20or%20obesity%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20just%20too%20short%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20just%20scratching%20the%20surface%20on%20better%20understanding%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20parents%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20young%20onset%3A%20was%20their%20exposure%20part%20of%20it%2C%20or%20not%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20five%20things%20we're%20learning%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c0e92369-92ea-430b-ac14-e0de33b280c0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Sleep%20cycle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20can't%20separate%20gut%20health%20from%20our%20internal%20clock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGut%20bacteria%20help%20regulate%20sleep%2C%20which%20cuts%20cancer%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmerging%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20disrupting%20the%20circadian%20rhythm%20creates%20problems%20in%20the%20gut%20that%20can%20contribute%20to%20colon%20cancer%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fsciadv.ado1458%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudies%20in%20mice%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjhoonline.biomedcentral.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs13045-022-01238-y%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20in%20humans%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Our%20sleep%20can%20be%20derailed%20by%20late%20schedules%20and%20artificial%20light%20from%20our%20homes%20and%20phones%2C%20which%20may%20be%20one%20factor%20in%20rising%20colon%20cancer%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2236473e62-bcb7-4631-ba90-a6f44f527f1d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Microplastics%20in%20air%20and%20water%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20researchers%20are%20finding%20evidence%20that%20microplastics%20play%20a%20negative%20role%20in%20fertility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20also%20be%20pro-inflammatory%2C%20driving%20diseases%20like%20cancer%20and%20obesity%2C%20hurting%20lungs%2C%20and%20possibly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fysph.yale.edu%2Fnews-article%2Fyale-study-forever-chemicals-promote-cancer-cell-migration%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelping%20cancer%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20thrive%20in%20the%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20evidence%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.acs.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1021%2Facs.est.3c09524%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroundup%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20researchers%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ucsf.edu%2Fnews%2F2024%2F12%2F429161%2Fmicroplastics-air-may-be-leading-lung-and-colon-cancers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUCSF%3C%2Fa%3E%20analyzed%2022%20studies%20that%20compared%20microplastic%20exposure%20to%20health%20problems%20in%20mice%20and%20people%2C%20and%20found%20that%20all%20of%20them%20showed%20some%20harm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20basically%20saw%20this%20continuous%20effect%20that%20the%20more%20you%20get%20exposed%20to%20it%2C%20so%20in%20our%20environment%2C%20the%20more%20it%20gets%20produced%2C%20the%20greater%20the%20health%20harm%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicholas%20Chartres%2C%20one%20of%20the%20study's%20authors%20and%20a%20former%20head%20of%20the%20science%20and%20policy%20team%20at%20UCSF's%20program%20on%20reproductive%20health%20and%20the%20environment%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChartres%20says%20the%20time%20is%20now%20to%20act%20to%20reduce%20our%20microplastic%20exposure%2C%20and%20it%20must%20be%20done%20at%20a%20policy%20level.%20At%20home%2C%20Chartres%20runs%20around%20the%20house%20throwing%20out%20his%20kids'%20plastic%20toys%2C%20but%20he%20knows%20he's%20playing%20a%20losing%20game%20of%20environmental%20whack-a-mole.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20need%20to%20have%20specific%20quantification%20of%20the%20level%20of%20harm%2C%20there's%20enough%20here%20to%20show%20that%20they're%20certainly%20contributing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221da73732-8347-4dc9-8a00-0887a32d604e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20What%20your%20parents%20were%20exposed%20to%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ELenz%20is%20conducting%20research%20that%20aims%20to%20unravel%20why%20so%20many%20Hispanic%20patients%20in%20Southern%20California%20seem%20to%20be%20especially%20at%20risk%20of%20developing%20early%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20team%20is%20studying%20cancer%20patients'%20blood%2C%20DNA%20damage%2C%20lifestyles%2C%20and%20ZIP%20codes%20to%20pinpoint%20where%20their%20exposure%20risks%20might%20be%20coming%20from%2C%20whether%20it%20be%20overuse%20of%20antibiotics%2C%20pollution%20that%20families%20are%20exposed%20to%2C%20or%20something%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20could%20be%20an%20epigenetic%20event%2C%20not%20only%20from%20the%20patient%20itself%20but%20from%20the%20family%2C%20from%20the%20parents%20and%20their%20exposure%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEpigenetics%20can%20be%20influenced%20by%20lifestyle%20and%20by%20exposure%20to%20chemicals%2C%20or%20whatever%20it%20is%20that%20will%20actually%20react.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f46ef91-7fe5-432f-b39c-827fe27d61dc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Antibiotics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20well%20established%20that%20antibiotics%20disrupt%20the%20gut%20microbiome%2C%20killing%20off%20some%20beneficial%20bacteria.%20And%20humans%20aren't%20the%20only%20antibiotic%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20antibiotics%20(73%25)%20in%20use%20worldwide%20are%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC7766021%2F%23B9-antibiotics-09-00918%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeat%20production%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20recent%20research%20suggests.%20Some%20meat%20advertised%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usda.gov%2Fabout-usda%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2024%2F08%2F28%2Fusda-releases-updated-guideline-strengthen-substantiation-animal-raising-and-environment-related%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eantibiotic-free%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20failed%20independent%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERed%20meat%20consumption%20ups%20a%20person's%20colon%20cancer%20risk%2C%20and%20so%20does%20antibiotic%20use%2C%20but%20these%20two%20factors%20aren't%20necessarily%20separate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223189a858-1669-496c-ad4c-f1e91acefa15%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20C-section%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENewborns%20are%20exposed%20to%20trillions%20of%20their%20mother's%20microbes%20as%20they%20travel%20through%20the%20birth%20canal%2C%20giving%20an%20infant's%20microbiome%20an%20initial%20boost.%20Kids%20who%20are%20delivered%20through%20the%20abdomen%20via%20cesarean%20section%20don't%20get%20those%20same%20health%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamanetworkopen%2Ffullarticle%2F2804228%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20from%20Sweden%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20girls%20who%20are%20born%20via%20c-section%20have%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20developing%20young%20colon%20cancer%20than%20those%20born%20vaginally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bbf53986-040f-4f4d-a63c-5ed3be94902f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajor%20colon%20cancer%20discoveries%20coming%20in%202025-2026%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20a%20group%20of%20international%20researchers%20mapped%201.6%20million%20cells%20in%20the%20gut%20to%20create%20the%20most%20comprehensive%20picture%20to%20date%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gutcellatlas.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egut%20atlas%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20rare%20that%20any%20one%20study%20squeezes%20out%20all%20the%20relevant%20biological%20insights%2C%26quot%3B%20Ivan%20Vujkovic-Cvijin%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20medicine%20at%20Cedars-Sinai%20Medical%20Center%2C%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20study%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20identifying%20which%20components%20of%20tissue%20function%20are%20dysregulated%20in%20disease%2C%20the%20scientific%20community%20can%20design%20drugs%20to%20restore%20those%20functions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20more%20to%20come.%20Multiple%20big%2C%20well-funded%20multinational%20studies%20are%20underway%2C%20including%20a%20US-UK%20collaboration%20that's%20giving%20out%20interdisciplinary%20cancer%20grants%20to%20teams%20around%20the%20world.%20The%20studies%20are%20expected%20to%20release%20results%20this%20year%20and%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2222e0a0f0-9070-4b5d-8ae7-cca228b624d3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2%20ways%20to%20reduce%20your%20risk%20today%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20we%20know%20better%20what's%20going%20on%2C%20researchers%20and%20clinicians%20say%20there%20are%20two%20steps%20you%20can%20take%20to%20reduce%20colon%20cancer%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20control%20what%20you%20can%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20focus%20on%20the%20stuff%20we%20can%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Cassandra%20Fritz%2C%20a%20gastroenterologist%20and%20colon%20cancer%20researcher%20at%20the%20Washington%20University%20School%20of%20Medicine%20in%20St.%20Louis%2C%20tells%20her%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20no%20smoking%2C%20regular%20exercise%2C%20less%20alcohol%2C%20reducing%20your%20intake%20of%20ultra-processed%20snacks%20and%20processed%20meats%2C%20and%20no%20sugary%20beverages%20%E2%80%94%20factors%20directly%20linked%20with%20colon%20cancer%20risk.%20You%20could%20also%20consider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastic-reduce-exposure-consumption-at-home-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicrowaving%20food%20in%20glass%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20ceramic%20instead%20of%20plastic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20know%20the%20signs%20of%20colon%20cancer%20and%20do%20not%20be%20complacent%20about%20them.%20Many%20young%20cases%20are%20diagnosed%20too%20late%2C%20making%20treatment%20complicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20four%20symptoms%20can%20occur%20up%20to%2018%20months%20before%20a%20colon%20cancer%20diagnosis%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAbnormal%20diarrhea%20that%20lasts%20for%20weeks%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPersistent%20abdominal%20pain%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBloody%20stool%20(red%2C%20magenta%2C%20or%20black)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIron%20deficiency%20anemia%20(determined%20by%20a%20blood%20test)%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20fear%20the%20process%20of%20getting%20checked%2C%20experts%20told%20BI.%20Anyone%20dealing%20with%20these%20persistent%20symptoms%20can%20ask%20their%20doctor%20for%20a%20fecal%20immunochemical%20test%20(FIT)%20that%20is%20noninvasive%20and%20costs%20just%20a%20few%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20there%20are%20symptoms%20which%20could%20be%20associated%20with%20colon%20cancer%2C%20make%20sure%20you%20get%20the%20screening%20and%20don't%20just%20accept%20that%20they're%20saying%20'It's%20unlikely'%20or%20'I've%20never%20seen%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20Lenz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it's%20spotted%20early%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww3.mdanderson.org%2Fapp%2Fmedcalc%2Findex.cfm%3Fpagename%3Dcoloncancer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%20is%20a%20very%20survivable%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-environmental-causes-microplastics-antibiotics-sleep-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737190801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67619ae7d610a4acda56af67%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-environmental-causes-microplastics-antibiotics-sleep-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20rising%20rate%20of%20colon%20cancer%20in%20young%20people%20can't%20be%20caused%20by%20diet%20alone%2C%20doctors%20say.%20Microplastics%2C%20sleep%2C%20and%20antibiotics%20may%20play%20a%20role.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hbrueck%40businessinsider.com%20(Hilary%20Brueck%2CGabby%20Landsverk%2CMia%20de%20Graaf)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-environmental-causes-microplastics-antibiotics-sleep-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nightclubs%20are%20bumping%2C%20traffic%20is%20snarled%2C%20and%20top%20restaurants%20are%20booked.%20Welcome%20to%20Palm%20Beach%20under%20Trump.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20is%20partying%20in%20Cucina%20club%20at%20Palm%20Beach.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678ab19dae09223df2ba84c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20man%20at%20the%20Cucina%20nightclub%20in%20Palm%20Beach.%3Cp%3EMartin