thebetterindia.com%2F345161%2Ftvaran-by-cisco-villgro-empower-women-led-startups-female-entrepreneurs-climate-action%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuilding%20a%20business%20as%20a%20woman%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%201920s%2C%20required%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20intrepidity.%20And%20Nataline%20left%20no%20stone%20unturned.%20Brian%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20grandmother%20used%20to%20work%20really%20hard.%20In%20those%20days%2C%20Pune%20was%20mostly%20jungle%20land.%20So%2C%20she%20would%20cycle%20to%20the%20market%20at%204.30%20am%20to%20buy%20the%20ingredients%20she%20needed%20and%20put%20it%20on%20a%20bullock%20cart%2C%20which%20would%20then%20bring%20it%20back%20to%20the%20factory%20to%20be%20cooked%20and%20processed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20would%20meticulously%20record%20her%20recipes%20in%20a%20book%2C%20a%20sort%20of%20archive%20of%20food%20memories%2C%20which%20the%20family%20still%20holds%20on%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECarrying%20on%20an%20alimentary%20legacy%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFerns%E2%80%99%20Pickles%20has%20seen%20three%20generations%20of%20expertise.%20And%20Brian%20sees%20this%20as%20a%20testament%20to%20the%20brand%E2%80%99s%20legacy.%20The%20secret%2C%20he%20says%2C%20lies%20in%20continuously%20pushing%20the%20envelope%2C%20a%20trait%20he%20picked%20up%20from%20his%20father%20George.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20my%20grandmother%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20well%20in%201960%2C%20my%20father%2C%20who%20was%20in%20the%20merchant%20navy%20at%20the%20time%2C%20quit%20and%20took%20over%20the%20business.%20In%20the%2070s%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F263689%2Findia-nilons-pickles-iconic-brands-suresh-prafful-sanghavi-inspiring%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epickle%20bottles%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20wrapped%20in%20straw%20and%20put%20into%20wooden%20boxes%20and%20exported.%20But%20the%20journey%20through%20the%20sea%20